The paper discusses a method for promoting sparsity in deep neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The use of regularization techniques is also a common approach in this field. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents an algorithm for solving the proposed model, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
